\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 # Workflow Implementation Design: KB-7 PostgreSQL \uc0\u8594  GraphDB Ingestion
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Let me provide a comprehensive workflow design that bridges the gap between your **Knowledge Factory pipeline** (the 3-tool system) and the **CDC-driven synchronization** we discussed earlier.
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## \uc0\u55356 \u57263  Critical Clarification: Two Distinct Data Flows
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Before we design the workflow, we need to understand that KB-7 has **two separate data flows** that must NOT be confused:
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### **Flow 1: Knowledge Factory \uc0\u8594  GraphDB (Primary Ontology Load)**
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Source**: External terminology providers (NCTS, LOINC.org, NIH RxNorm)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Processing**: SNOMED-OWL-Toolkit + ROBOT + Python converters
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Destination**: GraphDB (Layer 1 Authoritative Core)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Frequency**: Monthly releases (or on-demand)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Data Type**: Large RDF/OWL files (2.5M+ triples)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Purpose**: Load the **semantic knowledge** (medical concepts, hierarchies, mappings)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### **Flow 2: GraphDB \uc0\u8594  PostgreSQL Registry (Metadata Tracking)**
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Source**: GraphDB (after Knowledge Factory load)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Processing**: Metadata extraction + version tagging
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Destination**: PostgreSQL `kb7_snapshots` table
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Frequency**: After each Knowledge Factory build
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Data Type**: Small metadata records (1 row per kernel version)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Purpose**: Enable CDC detection + audit trail
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Your Question**: "Ingesting data from KB-7 PostgreSQL to GraphDB"
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **My Analysis**: This appears to be asking about the **reverse direction** (PostgreSQL \uc0\u8594  GraphDB), which would be **architecturally incorrect** for your system. Here's why:
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## \uc0\u10060  Why PostgreSQL \u8594  GraphDB is NOT Recommended
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### **Architectural Principle**: GraphDB is the Source of Truth for Ontologies
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Your PostgreSQL Registry serves three purposes:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 1. **Version Control**: Track which kernel versions exist
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 2. **Governance**: Record who approved releases and when
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 3. **CDC Trigger**: Signal to downstream systems that a new kernel is ready
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **PostgreSQL does NOT store**:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - SNOMED concepts (520,000 nodes)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - RxNorm drug hierarchies
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - LOINC lab codes
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Ontology relationships (1.3M triples)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **GraphDB stores all of the above** because:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - It's optimized for RDF triples and semantic reasoning
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - It supports SPARQL queries for complex graph traversals
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - It handles OWL inference (subsumption, classification)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Attempting to load PostgreSQL \uc0\u8594  GraphDB would mean**:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Storing 2.5M triples as PostgreSQL rows (performance nightmare)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Reimplementing semantic reasoning in SQL (impossible)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Losing OWL validation capabilities
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## \uc0\u9989  The Correct Flow: Knowledge Factory \u8594  GraphDB \u8594  PostgreSQL Registry
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Let me provide the **complete workflow** from source terminology to CDC-ready metadata.
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## **Phase 1: Knowledge Factory Build (External Sources \uc0\u8594  GraphDB)**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 This is where your 3-tool pipeline operates.
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### **Step 1: Source Acquisition**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Trigger**: Monthly release detection or manual trigger
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Actions**:
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 1. **SNOMED-CT Acquisition**:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Source: NCTS (National Clinical Terminology Service) - Australia
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Endpoint: https://www.healthterminologies.gov.au/
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Authentication: API credentials from Australian Digital Health Agency
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- File: `SnomedCT_AU_Release_20240331.zip` (RF2 format)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Size: ~450MB compressed
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 2. **RxNorm Acquisition**:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Source: NIH National Library of Medicine
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Endpoint: https://www.nlm.nih.gov/research/umls/rxnorm/
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- File: `RxNorm_full_20240304.zip` (RRF format)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Size: ~800MB compressed
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 3. **LOINC Acquisition**:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Source: LOINC.org (Regenstrief Institute)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Endpoint: https://loinc.org/downloads/
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Authentication: Free account + terms acceptance
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- File: `LOINC_2.77.zip` (CSV + XML)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Size: ~120MB compressed
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 4. **Verification**:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Check SHA-256 checksums against official release notes
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Validate digital signatures (if provided)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Store raw files in artifact repository (Nexus/Artifactory)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Output**: Three validated, versioned source archives
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### **Step 2: Transformation (3-Tool Pipeline)**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Environment**: GitHub Actions runner or Jenkins executor with Docker
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Execution**:
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **2A: SNOMED-CT Processing**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Tool: SNOMED-OWL-Toolkit
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Input: SnomedCT_AU_Release_20240331.zip
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Command:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/data snomed/owl-toolkit:latest \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0-rf2-to-owl \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0-rf2-snapshot-archives /data/SnomedCT_AU_Release_20240331.zip \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0-output-file /data/snomed-au-20240331.owl
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Processing:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Extract RF2 Snapshot files
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Read sct2_Concept_Snapshot_AU_20240331.txt (520,000 concepts)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Read sct2_Relationship_Snapshot_AU_20240331.txt (1.2M relationships)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Read sct2_Description_Snapshot_AU_20240331.txt (1.8M terms)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Map to OWL format with SNOMED namespace
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Duration: ~8 minutes
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Output: snomed-au-20240331.owl (1.8M triples)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **2B: RxNorm Processing**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Tool: Custom Python script (rxnorm_converter.py)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Input: RxNorm_full_20240304.zip
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Execution:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/data python:3.11-slim \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0python /data/rxnorm_converter.py \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--input /data/rrf/ \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--output /data/rxnorm-20240304.ttl
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Processing:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Parse RXNCONSO.RRF (drug concepts: 180,000 entries)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Parse RXNREL.RRF (relationships: 450,000 entries)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Parse RXNSAT.RRF (attributes: 320,000 entries)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Map to RDF triples with RXNORM namespace
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Duration: ~5 minutes
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Output: rxnorm-20240304.ttl (500,000 triples)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **2C: LOINC Processing**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Tool: Custom Python script (loinc_converter.py)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Input: LOINC_2.77.zip
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Processing:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Parse Loinc.csv (lab codes: 95,000 entries)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Parse LoincPartFile.csv (components: 28,000 entries)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Map to RDF with LOINC namespace
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Duration: ~2 minutes
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Output: loinc-2.77.ttl (200,000 triples)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **2D: ROBOT Merge**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Tool: ROBOT
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Command:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/work obolibrary/robot:latest \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0merge \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--input /work/snomed-au-20240331.owl \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--input /work/rxnorm-20240304.ttl \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--input /work/loinc-2.77.ttl \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--input /work/mappings/snomed-icd10-crosswalk.ttl \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--output /work/merged-ontology.owl
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Processing:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Combine all ontologies into single graph
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Resolve namespace conflicts
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Unify base URIs
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Duration: ~3 minutes
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Output: merged-ontology.owl (2.5M triples)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **2E: ROBOT Reason**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Tool: ROBOT + ELK Reasoner
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Command:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/work obolibrary/robot:latest \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0reason \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--input /work/merged-ontology.owl \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--reasoner ELK \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--create-new-ontology false \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--annotate-inferred-axioms true \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--output /work/reasoned-ontology.owl
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Processing:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Classify ontology (compute subsumption hierarchy)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Materialize inferred axioms
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Example inference:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0"Amoxicillin \uc0\u8594  is_a \u8594  Penicillin \u8594  is_a \u8594  Beta-lactam \u8594  is_a \u8594  Antibiotic"
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0Pre-computed so GraphDB doesn't compute at query time
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Duration: ~12 minutes (CPU-intensive)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Output: reasoned-ontology.owl (2.8M triples with inferred axioms)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **2F: ROBOT Verify (Quality Gates)**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Tool: ROBOT
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Command:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/work obolibrary/robot:latest \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0verify \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--input /work/reasoned-ontology.owl \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--queries /work/validation/*.sparql \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0--output-dir /work/results/
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Validation Queries:
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 1. check_missing_labels.sparql:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0"Find concepts without rdfs:label"
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0Expected: 0 results
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 2. check_dangling_references.sparql:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0"Find relationships pointing to non-existent concepts"
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0Expected: 0 results
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 3. check_snomed_coverage.sparql:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0"Count SNOMED concepts with Australian dialect terms"
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0Expected: >95% coverage
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 4. check_mapping_completeness.sparql:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0"Count SNOMED concepts with ICD-10-AM mappings"
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0Expected: >80,000 mappings
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 5. check_circular_hierarchies.sparql:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0"Find cycles in IS-A relationships"
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0Expected: 0 results
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Success Criteria:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- All queries return expected results
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Exit code: 0
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Failure Handling:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- If any query fails: Exit code 1
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- GitHub Actions marks build as FAILED
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Create GitHub Issue with validation report
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Alert clinical team via Slack/PagerDuty
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- DO NOT proceed to GraphDB load
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Duration: ~5 minutes
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Output: validation-report.txt (pass/fail per query)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Total Pipeline Duration**: ~35 minutes (for full build)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ---
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### **Step 3: Load to GraphDB (Authoritative Core)**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Trigger**: ROBOT verify passes (exit code 0)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Environment**: GraphDB server with preload utility
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Actions**:
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **3A: Prepare Import Configuration**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \

