\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## **Alternative Scenario: PostgreSQL as Primary Store (Not Recommended)**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 If you insist on storing ontology data in PostgreSQL first, here's why it's problematic:
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### **Challenges**:
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 1. **Schema Complexity**:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- RDF triples: Subject-Predicate-Object requires 3-column table
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- 2.8M triples = 2.8M rows (minimum)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Indexing: Need 6 indexes (SPO, SOP, PSO, POS, OSP, OPS) for query performance
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Storage: ~10GB just for indexes
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 2. **Semantic Reasoning**:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- PostgreSQL cannot perform OWL inference
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- SPARQL queries not natively supported
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Graph traversal (find all descendants) requires recursive CTEs (slow)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 3. **Performance**:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- GraphDB query: "Find all antihypertensive drugs" = 12ms
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- PostgreSQL equivalent (recursive CTE): 800ms+
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- 67x slower for typical semantic queries
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 4. **Maintenance**:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- Updating ontology = UPDATE 2.8M rows (locks entire table)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0- GraphDB update = Replace named graph (atomic operation)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### **If You Must Use PostgreSQL**:
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Option 1: PostgreSQL as Cache** (After GraphDB)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Table: kb7_triple_cache
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Columns:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0id \'a0 \'a0 \'a0 \'a0 BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0subject\'a0 \'a0 TEXT\'a0 \'a0 \'a0 NOT NULL
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0predicate\'a0 TEXT\'a0 \'a0 \'a0 NOT NULL
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0object \'a0 \'a0 TEXT\'a0 \'a0 \'a0 NOT NULL
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0graph_uri\'a0 TEXT\'a0 \'a0 \'a0 NOT NULL
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Indexes:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0CREATE INDEX idx_spo ON kb7_triple_cache (subject, predicate, object);
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0CREATE INDEX idx_graph ON kb7_triple_cache (graph_uri);
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Population:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- After GraphDB load succeeds
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Run SPARQL CONSTRUCT query
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Stream results into PostgreSQL
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Use COPY command for bulk insert (faster than INSERTs)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Duration: ~20 minutes to copy 2.8M triples
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Use Case:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- Simple lookups: "What's the label for SNOMED code X?"
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0- NOT for graph traversal or inference
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 **Option 2: PostgreSQL with JSON Storage**
