\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Knowledge Factory Implementation: The 3-Tool PipelineObjective: To automate the extraction, transformation, and validation of SNOMED-CT, RxNorm, and LOINC into a single, validated RDF Graph.The Pipeline Runner: GitHub Actions / JenkinsThe Output: kb7-kernel-v\{version\}.trig (A valid RDF dataset)Tool 1: SNOMED-OWL-Toolkit (The SNOMED Handler)Purpose: Convert SNOMED's proprietary "RF2" format (a complex set of tab-delimited files) into standard OWL ontology format.Source: IHTSDO/snomed-owl-toolkitDocker Image: snomed/owl-toolkit:latestThe Technical Workflow:Extract: The pipeline unzips the SNOMED release file (e.g., SnomedCT_InternationalRF2_PRODUCTION_20250301.zip).Execute: We run the toolkit in "RF2 to OWL" mode.# Implementation Command
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 java -jar snomed-owl-toolkit.jar \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0-rf2-to-owl \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0-rf2-snapshot-archives SnomedCT_InternationalRF2_PRODUCTION_20250301.zip \\
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0-output-file snomed-output.owl
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 What it does under the hood:It reads the Snapshot directory of the RF2 archive (the "current state" of all concepts).It maps the SNOMED concept model (Concept ID 12345) to an IRI: http://snomed.info/id/12345.It translates RF2 relationships (SourceId, DestinationId, TypeId) into OWL Object Properties: Subject SubClassOf (Property some Object).Output: snomed-output.owl (A valid, massive OWL ontology file).Tool 2: RRF-to-RDF Converter (The RxNorm Handler)Purpose: RxNorm comes as .RRF files (Rich Release Format), which are essentially relational database dumps (pipe-delimited). There is no "standard" tool for this, so we use a custom, optimized Python/Pandas script.Key Files to Process:RXNCONSO.RRF: Concepts and Names (The Nodes).RXNREL.RRF: Relationships (The Edges).RXNSAT.RRF: Attributes (The Properties).The Technical Workflow (Python Script):# rxnorm_converter.py (Simplified Logic)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 import pandas as pd
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 from rdflib import Graph, URIRef, Literal, Namespace
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 def convert_rxnorm(rrf_path, output_file):
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0g = Graph()
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0RXNORM = Namespace("http://purl.bioontology.org/ontology/RXNORM/")
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0# 1. Load Concepts (RXNCONSO)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0# Columns: RXCUI (ID), STR (Name), TTY (Term Type)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0conso = pd.read_csv(f"\{rrf_path\}/RXNCONSO.RRF", sep='|', usecols=[0, 12, 14], names=['RXCUI', 'TTY', 'STR'])
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0for index, row in conso.iterrows():
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0concept_uri = RXNORM[row['RXCUI']]
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0g.add((concept_uri, RDF.type, RXNORM.Concept))
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0g.add((concept_uri, RDFS.label, Literal(row['STR'])))
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0g.add((concept_uri, RXNORM.termType, Literal(row['TTY'])))
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0# 2. Load Relationships (RXNREL)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0# Columns: RXCUI1 (Source), RXCUI2 (Target), REL (Relationship Type)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0rel = pd.read_csv(f"\{rrf_path\}/RXNREL.RRF", sep='|', usecols=[0, 4, 7], names=['RXCUI1', 'RXCUI2', 'REL'])
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0for index, row in rel.iterrows():
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0source = RXNORM[row['RXCUI1']]
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0target = RXNORM[row['RXCUI2']]
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0predicate = RXNORM[f"has_\{row['REL']\}"] # e.g., has_isa, has_ingredient
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0g.add((source, predicate, target))
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0# 3. Serialize
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0g.serialize(destination=output_file, format='turtle')
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 if __name__ == "__main__":
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0convert_rxnorm("./input/rrf", "rxnorm-output.ttl")
